  "body": "# Bug Report\r\n\r\n\r\n## Problem \r\nWhen editing a message, expected that it will be updated on the receiver side everywhere. Currently push notification remains the same and pinned messages list is updated only after chat-reopening\r\n\r\n\r\n#### Expected behavior\r\nthe receiver can see updated messages\r\n\r\n#### Actual behavior\r\n1) PN is not updated: \r\nhttps://user-images.githubusercontent.com/4557972/232010780-9d6076a9-e2ec-4df5-a30c-8bb29da09e63.mp4 (`bbbb` instead `bbbb edit`)\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n### Reproduction\r\n**Prerequisites:** user A and User B are contacts, User B has PNs enabled \r\n\r\n1) User A: send message to user B\r\n2) User A: pin message\r\n3) User A: edit message\r\n4) User B: check message in pin messages list and check PN\r\n\r\n### Additional Information\r\n\r\n- Status version: nightly 14/03/23\r\n- Operating System: Android, iOS\r\n\r\n\r\n[comment]: # (Please, add logs/notes if necessary)\r\n\r\n",
